<subSubSection id="794F7D7B5528ABC7611D983B6A332174" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="28D2135EF3231F8E044ED28CF8A5DF2E" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0BAA9E210D995818C7A1C275D54BD39B" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName id="CF214103980B23590CB4170B87A7F9B7" authorityName="Padua &amp; Saeaeksjaervi" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Polysphincta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polysphincta bonita" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonita">
<emphasis id="0184F41B27BF3436008929EE52EAE4C1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Polysphincta bonita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="641A6B0A33219B43D74B9FA340042078" genus="P." lsidName="P. dizardi" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="dizardi">
<emphasis id="79381D9D8E6455E1959D9C8F31E914CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">P. dizardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by the combination of the following characters: (1) epomia absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2900DE29303FDA49834180BC498BD4E9" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Polysphincta bonita sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C face, anterior view D head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view E habitus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550742" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">1B</figureCitation>
); (2) malar space 0.5 times as long as proximal mandibular width (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="066DF6CC611ECAE0568B83627715530F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Polysphincta bonita sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C face, anterior view D head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view E habitus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550742" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">1B</figureCitation>
); (3) fore wing vein 1 
<emphasis id="F984ABFA485CF9A995242CCB1B19E8C8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">cu-a</emphasis>
interstitial relative to 
<emphasis id="D84C265C759DE7650E7DA97362F6837D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">M&amp;RS</emphasis>
; (4) mesosoma orange (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BFD1F24C2A195B85E0431D44030599B3" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Polysphincta bonita sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C face, anterior view D head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view E habitus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550742" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">1A</figureCitation>
); (5) wing hyaline, slightly infuscate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2E8FE6EE6917D52A5ED6F52F765FA83B" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Polysphincta bonita sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C face, anterior view D head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view E habitus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550742" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">1A</figureCitation>
); (6) hind leg brownish, except coxa orange and middle inner and outer region whitish (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4E041FD20A6E8B7DAB0771D8F2ED8A5F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Polysphincta bonita sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C face, anterior view D head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view E habitus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550742" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">1A</figureCitation>
); (7) metasoma with tergite I orange with posterior margin black, tergites II-IV brownish with anterior and anterolateral margins whitish and posterior margin black, and tergites V+ brownish (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="902AFBAD76B9828963F8ADAB60851AE3" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Polysphincta bonita sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C face, anterior view D head and shelf-like projection, dorsal view E habitus, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550742" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">1A, E</figureCitation>
); (8) ovipositor slightly slender, 1.0 times as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
